2026-04-28 | Minimum Operations to Make Grid Uni-Value

	Question
Return minimum operations needed.
	Key Insight
1.	All numbers must have same remainder modulo x:
		otherwise impossible  
2.	Convert grid → 1D array  
3.	To minimize operations:
		make all elements equal to the **median**  
(Why median? → minimizes sum of absolute differences)
	Approach
1.	Flatten grid into array  
2.	Check feasibility:
		(arr[i] - arr[0]) % x == 0 for all i  
3.	Sort array  
4.	Choose median  
5.	Compute operations:
		sum(|val - median| / x)  
	Time Complexity
	O(mn log(mn))
	Space Complexity
	O(mn)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int x) {
        vector<int> arr;
        for(auto &row : grid){
            for(int val : row){
                arr.push_back(val);
            }
        }
        // check feasibility
        for(int val : arr){
            if((val - arr[0]) % x != 0)
                return -1;
        }
        sort(arr.begin(), arr.end());
        int median = arr[arr.size()/2];
        int ops = 0;
        for(int val : arr){
            ops += abs(val - median) / x;
        }
        return ops;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Two critical observations:
1.	Feasibility → all values must align modulo x  
2.	Optimal target → median minimizes total moves  
This converts problem into a classic:
		minimum absolute difference optimization.
